<%- include('partials/header', { currentPage: 'credits', pageTitle: 'Credits' }) %>
        
        <section class="settings-section">
            <h2>About yt-down</h2>
            <p>Version <%= appVersion %></p>
            <p>A web application for queueing downloads using yt-dlp.</p>
            <h2>Dependencies</h2>
            <p>yt-down is essentially a wrapper for the <a href="https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp"><tt>yt-dlp</tt></a> command with a bit of queuing. <tt>yt-dlp</tt> leans on <a href="https://ffmpeg.org"><tt>ffmpeg</tt></a> for video processing.</p>
            
            <h3>Tool Versions</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>yt-dlp:</strong> 
                    <% if (toolVersions.ytDlp) { %>
                        <%= toolVersions.ytDlp %>
                    <% } else { %>
                        <span class="text-muted">Not available</span>
                    <% } %>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>ffmpeg:</strong> 
                    <% if (toolVersions.ffmpeg) { %>
                        <%= toolVersions.ffmpeg %>
                    <% } else { %>
                        <span class="text-muted">Not available</span>
                    <% } %>
                </li>
            </ul>
            
            <h2>Attributions</h2>
            <p>SVG symbols from <a href="https://lucide.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Lucide</a>, licensed under the <a href="https://lucide.dev/license" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ISC License</a>.</p>
        
            <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
            <p>There's a constant <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_Queen_hypothesis">Red Queen</a> battle between streaming platforms and utilities like <tt>yt-dlp</tt> that almost guarantees that this will break at some point. You could check this by running <tt>yt-dlp</tt> at your command line on the same link. If it's simply a matter of using a newer version of yt-dlp, the Docker version will probably have been updated accordingly.</p>
        </section>
        
        <%- include('partials/footer') %>
    </div>
    
    <script src="/js/websocket.js"></script>
</body>
</html>